16/11/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Swedish Foreign Minister Carl Bildt paid visits to Belgrade and Zagreb on Wednesday (November 15th) as part of his Balkan tour. In Belgrade, he met with President Boris Tadic to discuss Serbia's aim of resuming negotiations on a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU. They also talked about co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal, as well as about the Kosovo status issue. 
In Zagreb, Bildt met with his counterpart Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic, telling her he is confident that Croatia's goals of joining the EU and participating in the 2009 elections for European Parliament are realistic. 
EU integration prospects also dominated discussions Grabar-Kitarovic had on Wednesday with visiting Austrian Foreign Minister Ursula Plassnik. Plassnik stressed that although there are difficulties ahead for Croatia, there is also much room for optimism. (Tanjug, Beta, HINA - 15/11/06)
